                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Having "only" 43 AA to my name so far, I have had to make a lot of decisions on which AA to get first and which ones to get later.  For me personally, here is the way that I prioritized AA purchases:
<br />

<br />
At lev 64, I only had 6AA to my name in general abilities.  I found myself often going out of mana in the quick pullfests of LDON adventures.  Add to that I was starting to group with uber 65s that would shrug off 4 at a time, and it was no surprise that my mana was going quickly.  Due to this, my first priority was to improve my mana abilities, getting SCM3 and MC1.
<br />

<br />
After mana was no longer a big issue for me, my next focus became survivability.  I found myself declinining offers for LDON hard missions just because I couldn't survive long enough in there if I got a mez resist.  As a result, I have begun a focus to get CA3 and LR5.  So far I have CA2, however I got side tracked by another area...
<br />

<br />
DPS.  Classes tend to fall in one of 4 categories.  Tank, Healer, Slower, DPS.  Enchanters definitely fall into the slower category, and with our cc abilities we are in high demand.  But what about dps?  If I can be in the high end of dps compared to most classes, then that has added to my attractiveness as a group member (plus more dps means I get more AA faster).  As a result, I have put off getting CA3 for now, and am instead trying to get DireCharm, as that should provide a significant dps addition to a group.  Afer that I will return my focus back to Survivability.
<br />

<br />
So do you agree with my approach for a "new" enchanter?  Improve mana abilities first, then survivability, then dps?</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
