                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You have not said much about your play style and raiding activities.
<br />

<br />
Given you mentionioning LDoN, I would probably say the Gather Mana may be a bit too spendy for "the next" thing to get.  ER3 is <span style="text-decoration: underline">strongly</span> recommended if you do not already have it, it'll increase your survuvablity greatly. SCM3 and MC3 are nice and will show a vast improvment on the mana bar.  
<br />

<br />
Offensive class?  For LDoN either you can go the Animation Empathy or the regular charm route.  AnimEmp is very safe but will only add 10-30 DPS, you results may vary.  Charming on the other hand will give you outstanding DPS but also the inherant risk of charm breaks at the wrong time.  DC for LDoN is out of the question as there is nothing that I have ever seen worth DCing.  We're not really designed as a DPS class without some kind of charm unfortunately.  At least one of the enchanters on the test server will tell you differently, she likes to chain insanity and ACV but it's highly unlikely that you have ACV and while her argument is compelling on paper it's shite in reality since most targets you'd be nuking have MR out the wazu.  If I recall, her figure was something like 90 DPS with those two spells under perfect circumstances, think of a reasonably equiped warrior = 90 DPS.  The "wow" factor of CF is ok but just so so in reality, with CF3 I can crit for 2200 and while it's nice to know you are contributing it sucks to see mage and wiz DD's flying by at 6k a pop.
<br />

<br />
If you raid a lot GM and MGB enter into the picture now as being essentials for raid buffing and for faster recoveries.  If you play in PoP a lot I would recomment DC, if you tradekill Anim Emp is great for farming greens....  
<br />

<br />
It's a big world with lots of choices, I'd start with ER3, then get the easy mana recovery/conservation AA's then roll on to defensive AA's like CA/LR.  At some point you will be tempted by the forbidden fruit and pick up DC, AnimEmp or TD.  
<br />

<br />
Enjoy!
<br />

<br />
Fin</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-style: italic"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal"><span style="color: green">Master Finbarr</span></span></span>
<br />
E Marr</span>
