                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Let's see, I got Run3 first.  Then I went the metabolism route instead of regen.  3 extra HP per tick isn't going to keep you alive, and a small heal from any class (ranger, shaman, druid, paladin) will solve minor missing HP a lot quicker than waiting for the regen.  Now I rarely have to worry about running out of food.  My horse eats alot, but the AAs tone it down.
<br />

<br />
After that I went for MGB because I was in a raiding guild. (Though I think there are pre-reqs so I couldn't get it right away.  I forget the exact order.)
<br />

<br />
I wanted Anim.Emp. just so I could finally tell that stupid animation what to do and make me feel a little more in control.
<br />

<br />
I got DC because it sounded like fun and seemed to be a defining AA for us.  (I also have an item with the Voice Graft effect.  This and DC make for tons of fun!)
<br />

<br />
I got Perm. Illusion and Project Illusion just for fun, though Perm.Ill. does have its uses.  Project Ill. is just fun.
<br />

<br />
I also got 2 levels of extended duration and 2 levels of regen mana (was planning on going for Gather Mana, but haven't gotten there yet).  The extended duration was kinda so I could sell KEI in PoK and have an advantage over others that may be doing it.  But I haven't sat in PoK doing this for long time.  I still want to get the third level, and then the Mastery level too.  With my 8th shawl, that means 65% extended duration on buffs.
<br />

<br />
I noticed I was getting a lot of resists on mezzes, when another enchanter didn't have near the problem.  He had many more AA than I, including the extended CHA cap.  I also wanted higher INT for when I do more trade skills, so I got the 5 AA extendeding the cap for all stats.  I don't get near as many resists on mezzes with 305 CHA, and charms seem to work better too.  (I think these AA are under-rated and strongly suggest you consider them.)
<br />

<br />
I don't have any TD, but I only charm in HoH and I don't have any problems.  Breaks yes, but it is easily handled, and they don't happen often.
<br />

<br />
I did get one level of Elritch Rune.  I'm not sure if I want to finish it off first, or do something else.  I like the idea of 65% extended duration buffs.
<br />

<br />
I probably should have gone for SCM3 to save mana, but I didn't realize its full potential at first.
<br />

<br />
Oh well, that's just my route.  I decided to get more "fun" AA then "useful" AA, and I don't regret it.  But your play-style will determine your route.
<br />

<br />

<br />
-- C.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
