                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There was a wonderful quote from an enchanter here, I forget who or the name of the thread but basically it went something like"
<br />

<br />
Take a rock, smash your hand with it.
<br />
Now cover your hand with a piece of cloth and smash your hand with the same rock.
<br />
That is enchanter damage mitigation.
<br />

<br />
That phrase, while funny, pretty much holds true.  We can not, and are not meant to, mitigate damage.  This is why we have runes of all sorts.  The defensive AAs that I have gotten (I think I have like CA 3 and LR3 now) have made little difference, if at all to my survivability.  If I could get those AAs back I would in a heart beat.  I remember reading somewhere you need over 1600ac to start mitigating damage from PoP mobs...I think I read that on a paladin forum EQKnights come to think of it.  Anyways, a caster making that kind of AC is not very common, you would need lots of Elemental gear to approach that number, which in all likely hood, won't happen unless you are in your servers top raiding guild.
<br />

<br />
Bottom line is, IMO, your best spent survivability AAs would be ER3 and mez mastery to fire off longer duration WoM.  Next get SCS to help reduce tashicide.  If you are really concerened about getting more hit points then get ND as well.  Personally I am not.  I get buffed up to around 5k hit points raid buffed.  If I get aggro in a raid, unless I have a quick draw healer in my group or a tank paying attention, I am going to probably die.  Hence why SCS is worth it's weight in gold, it has made a night and day difference to when I can start my casting on a mob.  Prior to that I was also nervous about tashing and crippling, but not anymore.
<br />

<br />
Oromet Andunie
<br />
65 Coercer
<br />
FV server</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
