                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">In regards to the last poster, I am not trying to increase my damage mitigation - I am trying to get hit less.  Everyone else seems to think that CA3/LR5 helps a lot, so I do plan to go that route.  While it is hard to say, I think that even with CA2, I am noticing a difference.  I don't have a hope in the world of mitigating my way out of GoD mobs.  (:  Eldritch Rune I have serious doubts about, especially since it doesn't stack with Arcane Rune, although I am sure that I will get it at some point.  Getting the Doppleganger instead sounds like more fun.  (:  I would love to get mez mastery, but I think I would quit the game before I got 20AA with no improvement.  Direcharm I was getting for PoP, and in theory those rare cases where I want to have fun and solo.  (I did get Direcharm last night).  I will get MC2 and MC3 eventually, but current mana situation is doable.  Gather Mana is very situational in use, and won't resolve regular issues with being low in mana.  I will probably get Secondary Forte before I get Gather Mana.  Quick Buff is something that is also on my wish list to help with survivability, although based on these comments I will wait until after I get ER.
