                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I squeeze and hug SCS much more then I squeeze and hug my defensive AAs.  Honestly if you think about it, if you have less chance to draw aggro by reducing the inherent aggro, tash or slow for example generate, then what is the point of putting CA and LR at the top of the list or near it if you are not drawing aggro.
<br />

<br />
Well think of it this way, everytime you cast, SCS is firing off and helping you.  How often is CA/LR helping you?  Only when a mob is attacking you.  If you reduce the amount of times the mob goes after you...then what's the point.  Well unless you solo a lot which I do and is why I started to put points into CA and LR.  However that Zek Initiate still hits me just as much as before I have noticed from when I had 0 Def AAs compared to now.  The only thing that keeps me kicking with out extended breaks is my runes.
<br />

<br />
IMO, the most bang for your buck/AA would be the way that I said...but everyone plays differently so you pick what you think sounds best  <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Oromet Andunie
