                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I spent a majority of the first 65 levels not even concerned with equipment.  The difference in my survivability, however had as much to do with my equipment as it did with my AA.  So, take it for what its worth, but equipment has really made a huge difference in my effectiveness.
<br />

<br />
My suggestions:  Mix your defensive and mana saving AA together.  You'll find that you work into the role of urber chanter that way.  IMO -- defensive would be: ER, CA/LR, ND, CS/ID.  ND is highly dependent upon equipment, however, so if you don't have the equipment, do that last.  For offensive AA, the ones you'll see the most improvement out of are those that improve your effectiveness of charming.  At the hard LDoN level, our dps is fairly subtle in what it can do to affect the group's overall dps output -- even with a charmed pet.  In GoD, that's changed somewhat (part of why they made the change to disallow pets in Kod'Taz and beyond).  After charming, our best dps is in nuking, so I recommend TD3 first and then the fury line.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
