                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well since nobody else has said it, I'd argue that Quick Buff is a great defensive spell.  ER is great, but since I got  QB3, I rarely use itl.  Now in fairness, I almost always have up Shield of Auras, which adds another 500hp dmg shield.
<br />

<br />
I actually never did get ER3....got it to ER2, and always seemed to get something else first.  At this point, it's no longer a high priority.
<br />

<br />
I would agree with most here that Gather Mana is not an essential AA.  It sounds great in theory, but I generally find that when I die, so do other casters.  If they have to rest, then GM normally doesn't help save anything.
<br />

<br />
It is useful, however, if I'm the only one caster who died or if I'm LOM and charming.
<br />

<br />
I have none of the anti-fizzle AAs, and they're very low on my list.  I just don't fizzle that often.
<br />

<br />
I'd skip DC if I could do it again....by the time I had it, it was fairly useless, though it's ok if you can find a mob to DC and regular charming is either too risky or the group is too scared of regular charms.
<br />

<br />
The new GoD ones are just so damn expensive, I'll have to decide when I get closer....the Mez one sounds very nice, as does Doppleganger.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Without my secret energy pill, I grow weaker and weaker and weaker still.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
