                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold">Best General Archetype AA</span> - Run 3
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Best Caster Archetype AA</span> - SCM 3
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Best Enchanter Archetype AA</span> - Quick Buff 3 (or QB2 + spell haste).
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Best Planar Advancement AA</span> - There are Planar Advancement AAs?
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Best Planar Ability AA</span> - Eldritch Rune 3
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Best GoD AA</span> - Mez Mastery
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Best Overall AA Availible to Enchanters</span> - Eldritch Rune 3
<br />

<br />
ER3 is an Instant-Cast Manaless Componentless 1500 HP self rune that doesn't cause your spells to have to refresh.  It only has a 10 minute refresh.  This AA is possibly one of the best of ANY class in the game.  I think it's a good buy at any level, but probably even better the 'younger' you are.  You can use it while running, inbetween mezzes while things are beating on you, or just if you need the rune and are really LOM.  Basically with Arcane Rune up and Eldritch Rune ready, it's like you have 3000 HP more than what's listed in your HP bar.  Eldritch Rune can't be interrupted, and basically the only times you can't cast it are when you are stunned, mezzed, or zoning.
<br />

<br />
There are two things that an enchanter should do at all costs.  The first of these is to not die.  The second of these is to do crowd control.  The second one is impossible if you fail at the first one.  A living enchanter can make impossible pulls possible.  When charming, a living enchanter can make awesome DPS not turn into horrible wipage -- so long as the enchanter is alive.  You *must* stay alive.  It's probably close to being as important as the healer staying alive.  If you have no healer, an enchanter can lock things down while waiting for an evac, rez, or CR.  If you have no enchanter, you have to hope that your healer has plenty of mana and HP or that there's an Exodus druid there in some cases.  Eldritch Rune 3 is the best thing that enchanters can get to help with their cause of staying alive.
<br />

<br />
Oh but what about Quick Buff!?!?!  No.  Sorry.  In 2.5 seconds, your Arcane Rune still can be interrupted by push or dumb movement.  You would still have to have spell gems refresh.  You would have to have that spell memmed.  (If you don't anyhow, you're dumb, but there have been times I have not memmed it for various reasons.)  You would also have to have mana for the spell.  But here's the kicker -- QB 3 is 18 AAs.  ER 3 is 9 AAs.  Even if you think the two abilities are close in power or that QB is slightly better than ER, then you would *still* have to pick ER since it's HALF the cost!
<br />

<br />
The only time to get QB 3 before ER 3 is when you don't have enough levels for ER, but really, you should just go to 65 before you get AA, with the possible exception of run3 for convenience.
<br />

<br />
/opinion off</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="http://www.blaynesucks.com/images/Bellanfear.gif" border="0" />
