		<td width="150" align="left" valign="top" class="row2"><a name="28983"></a><span class="name"><span class="usercolor">Axterix EnObelix</span></span><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_offline.gif" border="0" align="absbottom" alt="Offline" title="Offline" /><div class="gensmall"><img src="images/ranks/rank_7.gif" alt="<b><center>Sage</b></center>" title="<b><center>Sage</b></center>" border="0" /><br /><b><center>Sage</b></center></div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Joined:&nbsp;12 Aug 2003</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Total posts:&nbsp;437</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Gender:&nbsp;Unknown</div></td>
                <td class="row2" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                        <tr>
                                <td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=28983&amp;sid=a89249cc9b56b6a633b8a8cdd519a772#28983"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Mon Mar 08, 2004 2:23 pm<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
                                <td valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=28983&amp;sid=a89249cc9b56b6a633b8a8cdd519a772"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>    </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I would agree with most here that Gather Mana is not an essential AA. It sounds great in theory, but I generally find that when I die, so do other casters. If they have to rest, then GM normally doesn't help save anything.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I rarely use GM post death.  To me, it's the emergency mana pool.  As it is, I rarely run out of mana.  But when I do, I can pop GM, be back at full, and continue on.  If I used it post death, I'd lose that benefit.  Rather get back on my feet and get rolling, having GM to back me up if needed.  The odds of me running out of mana 2x within a short time frame are pretty low.  Because of GM, I don't have to worry as much about mana pool size, leaving me free to focus on +hp over +mana.  It also means that there's no reason to stop and med for safety reasons if I get low do to a spike in my mana usage.  Should a second such spike occur, I've got GM.  It's one of the few AAs where having, not the actual using of it, is the primary benefit.
<br />

<br />
Basically, it's piece of mind.  Well worth it.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Best GoD AA - Mez Mastery</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
