                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Axterix EnObelix wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> </span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Ilaanea wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I would agree with most here that Gather Mana is not an essential AA. It sounds great in theory, but I generally find that when I die, so do other casters. If they have to rest, then GM normally doesn't help save anything.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I rarely use GM post death.  To me, it's the emergency mana pool.  As it is, I rarely run out of mana.  But when I do, I can pop GM, be back at full, and continue on.  If I used it post death, I'd lose that benefit.  Rather get back on my feet and get rolling, having GM to back me up if needed.  The odds of me running out of mana 2x within a short time frame are pretty low.
<br />

<br />
Basically, it's piece of mind.  Well worth it.
<br />

<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Well that's  what I tend to use it for as well,  but the only time that's useful, for the most part, is in LDON if I'm charming and charm breaks quickly or near a very bad pull (mez mana drain).
<br />

<br />
But I have used it where I died and nobody else did.  If you're in LDON, saving several minutes by  avoiding meditation can be nice.....normally only happens, however, when the group is marginal.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Without my secret energy pill, I grow weaker and weaker and weaker still.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
