Obviously, if you're trying to get control of the mob (for re-mez or re-charm), you'll do nothing but run through mana with repeated AR, especially if it's a hasted, dual-wielding ex-pet, but that's not the scenario I was referring to.
<br />

<br />
If I'm in a hard LDoN or GoD, the tank isn't always going to be able to taunt off me in one round.  Most rounds are going to run through the equivalent of an AR/ER3 or more.  AR+QB3 is great for those situations where the tank just can't gain aggro for whatever reason (or is dead  <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" />  ).  ER is great to have for just the kind of situation you mention, but it's not going to do a bit of good for you if you have to take much more than one round of combat from the kind of mobs you're talking about.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Sage Velurian Soliqui, E'ci
